description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 3 Business Support to LAC Service within CPMS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a well organised and highly motivated full-time Business Support to join our Paediatric Medical Service and in particular supporting the Looked After Children (LAC) and Child Protection (CP) teams. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Paediatric Medical Service have a team of clinicians working in various venues across Southampton City and New Forest who deliver a comprehensive support to our families. We are looking for someone who is passionate about customer / patient experience with a ‘can do’ attitude.&lt;span&gt; The role requires liaison with outside services such as Social Services and The Police. &lt;/span&gt;The work in the Service is very wide and varied and you can be subject to some very sensitive and in some cases distressing information. Therefore, ensuring confidentiality at all times is essential together with being resilient and having a very calm and empathetic nature. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will be:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a good team player who can work both effectively as part of a team and on their own&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;able to use own initiative and apply a commonsense approach to problems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;have a meticulous eye for detail, an enquiring mind and a willingness to learn&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;strong communication skills with the ability to communicate effectively at all levels&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;be organised, able to multi-task, work under pressure and prioritise own workload&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;proven skills in Microsoft applications, Excel, Word and Outlook&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are looking for a new challenge, would like to join us in improving health outcomes for children and young people and can demonstrate your suitability for the role then we look forward to hearing from you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role is full-time 37.5 hours per week and having use of a car is preferable if needing to support a clinic not at your base. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please read the attached job description and person specification for more details and should you wish to discuss the role further please contact Diana Harrison on 07795 451 647.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that should this post attract sufficient interest, we may choose to close at an earlier date. We strongly suggest that you apply at an early stage.&lt;strong&gt;If we have not contacted you within four weeks of the closing date of this post, please presume that you have not been selected.&lt;/strong&gt;Candidates selected for interview will be contacted within 2-3 weeks; therefore you should check your emails regularly including junk mail folders.&lt;/p&gt;
